      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:45:7",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَمِيرُ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) النُّورَةُ نُشْرَةٌ وَ طَهُورٌ لِلْجَسَدِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Al Qasim Bin Yahya, from his grandfather Al Hassan Bin Rashid, from Abu Baseer, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘<span class=\"iTxt\">Al-Noura</span> is an advertisement (of beauty) and a cleanser for the body’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "7. Ahmad ibn Muhammad has narrated from al-Qasim ibn Yahya from his grandfather al-Hassan ibn Rashid from abu Basir who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that ’Amir al-Mu’minin has said, ‘Applying lime paste is a protective charm and purification (for the body).”’ "
        ]
      }
